<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
The relationships of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[533,725,1310,1339]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.bestMatchDistance="2190" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis box="[533,725,1310,1339]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not clear, but considering the similarities in familial structure and general appearance and the shared “ sex monomorphism” high number of ceratobranchial rakers, low ratio dorsal spines to dorsal rays (D. XIV-XV 8-9 in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" box="[661,844,1524,1553]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramírezí">
<emphasis box="[661,844,1524,1553]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramírezí</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) etc., they appear to be with 
<taxonomicName authority="Heckel" authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1840" box="[315,634,1576,1610]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Geophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,500,1576,1610]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Geophagus</emphasis>
Heckel
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Eigenmann &amp; Kennedy" authorityName="Eigenmann &amp; Kennedy" authorityYear="1903" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Biotodoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[718,898,1576,1604]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Biotodoma</emphasis>
Eigenmann &amp; Kennedy
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" box="[350,540,1683,1713]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramírezí">
<emphasis box="[350,540,1683,1713]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramírezí</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is certainly distinct from members of these genera and others with an epibranchial lobe as presently known in one or more of the following characters: position of epibranchial rakers, colour pattern, maximum size (less than 40 mm SL in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[528,719,1895,1927]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.bestMatchDistance="1851" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis box="[528,719,1895,1927]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), distance between upper lateral line and dorsal ﬁn, size of epibranchial lobe, number of supraneurals, depth of lacrimal and breeding behaviour, to mention but a few characters generally recognized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eigenmann &amp; Kennedy" authorityYear="1903" box="[172,352,2107,2136]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Biotodoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[172,352,2107,2136]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Biotodoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1840" box="[434,619,2108,2143]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Geophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[434,619,2108,2143]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Geophagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were recently revised by Gosse (1976). Although our knowledge of the species in these genera is now considerably expanded, we still lack material for a satisfactory explanation of the phylogeny of a “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1840" box="[952,1143,2267,2301]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Geophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[952,1143,2267,2301]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Geophagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group” of genera including 
<emphasis box="[586,846,2320,2355]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="SVEN O. KULLANDER" authorityYear="1977" box="[586,835,2320,2355]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Papiliochromis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
Further indication that 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[578,769,2374,2403]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.bestMatchDistance="1581" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis box="[578,769,2374,2403]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be more closely related 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[269,499,2426,2461]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1840" box="[314,499,2426,2461]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Geophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Geophagus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reproductive behaviour Monogamous, open-breeder, eggs laid on horizontal surfaces or in pits, brood-care biparental Polygynous, concealment breeder, eggs laid on vertical or rooﬁng surfaces, maternal brood-care" authorityYear="1913" box="[646,892,2427,2461]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[646,892,2427,2461]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Apistogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was presented by Wickler (1956) in a comparative study of egg-type and egg-attachment in cichlid ﬁshes (see also Wickler 1960). It is possible, however, that the egg-type is a function of incubation type and thus only a parameter of the reproductive behaviour in general, which is already very different in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramírezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramírezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reproductive behaviour Monogamous, open-breeder, eggs laid on horizontal surfaces or in pits, brood-care biparental Polygynous, concealment breeder, eggs laid on vertical or rooﬁng surfaces, maternal brood-care" authorityYear="1913" box="[364,609,2747,2781]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[364,609,2747,2781]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Apistogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., but similar in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" box="[960,1148,2748,2777]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramírezí">
<emphasis box="[960,1148,2748,2777]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramírezí</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a number of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heckel" authorityYear="1840" box="[422,606,2800,2834]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Geophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[422,606,2800,2834]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Geophagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
Scheel’s (1972) discussion of the karyotypes of a few cichlid species was probably not intended as a serious presentation of research results, judging from the title and the style, but certainly suggests karyotype differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reproductive behaviour Monogamous, open-breeder, eggs laid on horizontal surfaces or in pits, brood-care biparental Polygynous, concealment breeder, eggs laid on vertical or rooﬁng surfaces, maternal brood-care" authorityYear="1913" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Apistogramma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">Apistogramma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[452,640,3066,3096]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.bestMatchDistance="1176" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis box="[452,640,3066,3096]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Probably further studies will bring this out in detail.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="254">
A redescription of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander, 1977" authorityName="Kullander" authorityYear="1977" baseAuthorityName="Myers &amp; Harry" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[505,696,3172,3201]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Papiliochromis" genus.bestMatchDistance="1125" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="254" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis box="[505,696,3172,3201]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="254">P. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in preparation and will amplify our understanding of the new genus.
</paragraph>
